<taxonomicName authority="Asenjo &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, 2013" authorityName="Asenjo &amp; Ribeiro-Costa" authorityYear="2013" box="[892,1022,207,231]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marina" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Tropiochirus">
(
<emphasis box="[901,919,208,231]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">T</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[944,1022,208,231]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">marina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1029,1114,208,231]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
have the median sulcus of head deep, sides of the median sulcus parallel (
<figureCitation box="[979,1166,239,263]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[211,278,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[238,1145,161,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[238,1145,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Head and protorax of Leptochirus (Tropiochirus). (A) L. (T.) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">Figure 2D, G, B</figureCitation>
, respectively), but 
<emphasis box="[408,433,272,295]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">L.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Asenjo &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, 2013" authorityName="Asenjo &amp; Ribeiro-Costa" authorityYear="2013" box="[440,561,271,295]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milton" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Tropiochirus">
(
<emphasis box="[448,466,272,295]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">T</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[491,561,271,295]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">milton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[568,652,272,295]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from these species by the first dorsal tooth of the left mandible not bifurcate (
<figureCitation box="[793,913,303,327]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1078,1100]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetId="figure-6@6.[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Left and right mandible, dorsal view. (A) Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">Figure 3D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="1272" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[211,438,401,464]" box="[211,338,401,424]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">
<heading box="[211,338,401,424]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[211,338,401,424]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[211,438,401,464]" box="[211,438,440,464]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">BL: 12.67, BW: 2.35</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[211,925,504,528]" box="[211,925,504,528]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">Body strongly depressed. Body all black except tarsi red-brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[211,1172,568,878]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[211,279,568,592]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">Head.</emphasis>
Transverse (
<figureCitation box="[420,540,568,592]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[211,278,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[238,1145,161,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[238,1145,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Head and protorax of Leptochirus (Tropiochirus). (A) L. (T.) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">Figure 2D</figureCitation>
). Inner lateral teeth separated by a depression extending to base. Inner and outer lateral teeth fused and resembling a septum; median sulcus deep, sides of median sulcus parallel; laterofrontal depressions oval. Labrum with outer edge strongly angled and lateral-apical edge concave. Mandibles (
<figureCitation box="[1034,1167,663,687]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[211,278,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[238,1145,161,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[238,1145,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Head and protorax of Leptochirus (Tropiochirus). (A) L. (T.) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">Figures 2D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[211,246,695,719]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1078,1100]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetId="figure-6@6.[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Left and right mandible, dorsal view. (A) Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">3D</figureCitation>
) with lateral longitudinal ridge occupying less than two-thirds of apical region; external margin developed, attenuated anteriorly. Left mandible (
<figureCitation box="[939,1056,727,751]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1078,1100]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetId="figure-6@6.[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Left and right mandible, dorsal view. (A) Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">Figure 3D</figureCitation>
) with first dorsal tooth developed, straight and not bifurcate, accessory tooth near lateral longitudinal ridge; second dorsal tooth little developed and resembling a small hill; first ventral tooth with tooth accessory, third ventral tooth consisting of two structures with the bases fused. Submentum with setae arranged in a row on anterolateral margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[211,1172,918,1229]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[211,301,918,942]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[437,555,918,942]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[211,278,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[238,1145,161,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[238,1145,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Head and protorax of Leptochirus (Tropiochirus). (A) L. (T.) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">Figure 2D</figureCitation>
) a little wider than long (PL: 2.39, PW: 2.78); superior marginal line of hypomeron not interrupted, not bent to dorsal region on anterior margin and slightly bent to dorsal region at posterior margin; without a pair of small depressions near basal constriction. Inferior marginal line of hypomeron reaching anterior margin. Apex of prosternal process strongly expanded and resembling a circular plate, extending considerably beyond the lateral process of hypomeron. Metaventrite with microsculpture longitudinally undulate in the median region and with small longitudinal median depression near posterior edge. Mesoscutellum with apex rounded. Elytra longer than broad and without a pair of small depressions on posterolateral edge (EL: 2.91, EW: 2.69).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[211,1172,1269,1389]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[211,322,1269,1293]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Cylindrical. Sternite III with keel of apex rounded. Tergite IX (
<figureCitation box="[1044,1163,1269,1293]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="15.[211,278,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 6. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) milton sp. nov. holotype: (A) aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) pachoensis. (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) proteus. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">Figure 6D</figureCitation>
) sclerotized with left and right plates separated, each with five or six setae of various lengths. Tergite X (
<figureCitation box="[420,537,1333,1357]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="15.[211,278,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 6. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) milton sp. nov. holotype: (A) aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) pachoensis. (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) proteus. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">Figure 6D</figureCitation>
) membranous except for sclerotized apical part, with two pairs of long apical setae.
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="15" pageNumber="1271" startId="15.[211,278,1458,1480]">
<paragraph blockId="15.[211,1172,1458,1685]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">
Figure 6. 
<taxonomicName authority="Asenjo &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, 2013" authorityName="Asenjo &amp; Ribeiro-Costa" authorityYear="2013" box="[318,657,1458,1480]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milton" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Tropiochirus">
<emphasis box="[318,435,1458,1480]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">Leptochirus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[452,577,1458,1480]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">Tropiochirus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[594,657,1458,1480]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">milton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[666,746,1459,1480]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
holotype: (A) aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. 
<emphasis box="[937,953,1518,1539]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">L</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1917" box="[968,1121,1517,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachoensis" subGenus="Tropiochirus">
(
<emphasis box="[976,992,1518,1539]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">T</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1016,1121,1517,1539]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">pachoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. 
<taxonomicName box="[211,451,1604,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="proteus" subGenus="Tropiochirus">
<emphasis box="[211,328,1605,1627]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">Leptochirus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[342,358,1605,1626]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">T</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[379,451,1605,1626]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1271">proteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="16.[143,1103,167,383]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1272">
<emphasis box="[143,208,168,192]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1272">Male.</emphasis>
Sternite IX (
<figureCitation box="[358,474,167,191]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="15.[211,278,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 6. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) milton sp. nov. holotype: (A) aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) pachoensis. (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) proteus. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="16" pageNumber="1272">Figure 6E</figureCitation>
) composed of two plates, distal plate sclerotized except for membranous apex, anterior margin straight, posterior margin with small acute projection in the middle and with two long setae; proximal plate less sclerotized, greater than apical, broadened in middle and with a projecting angle at posterior bor- der. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[320,471,295,319]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="15.[211,278,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 6. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) milton sp. nov. holotype: (A) aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) pachoensis. (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) proteus. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="16" pageNumber="1272">Figure 6A–C</figureCitation>
) with median lobe slightly bulbous at base, rounded at apex, weakly sclerotized on dorsal side and a small plate sclerotized on ventral side; parameres short, pointed and fused dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[143,1103,422,510]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1272">
<emphasis box="[143,229,423,447]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1272">Female.</emphasis>
Similar to male, except for the gonocoxites divided longitudinally (
<figureCitation box="[975,1091,422,446]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="15.[211,278,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 6. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) milton sp. nov. holotype: (A) aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) pachoensis. (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) proteus. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="16" pageNumber="1272">Figure 6F</figureCitation>
). The distal plate with apex membranous and long seta; proximal plate with the posterior region pointed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
